[assistant] Fixed the failing tests by passing strategy class names instead of `Class` objects for the SQM strategy settings.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changed in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.1.0.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate/hibernate_core/SessionFactoryOptionsBuilderTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Specifically:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `DialectConstructorMutationStrategy.class` → `DialectConstructorMutationStrategy.class.getName()`
[assistant] - `DialectConstructorInsertStrategy.class` → `DialectConstructorInsertStrategy.class.getName()`
[assistant] - `EmptyConstructorMutationStrategy.class` → `EmptyConstructorMutationStrategy.class.getName()`
[assistant] - `EmptyConstructorInsertStrategy.class` → `EmptyConstructorInsertStrategy.class.getName()`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Reason: Hibernate `6.1.0.Final` reads `hibernate.query.mutation_strategy` using `ConfigurationHelper.extractPropertyValue`, which expects a `String`, so passing a `Class` causes the observed `ClassCastException`. The string class name still goes through Hibernate’s normal `StrategySelector` path and should reach the same `SessionFactoryOptionsBuilder` dynamic-access call sites.
[assistant-event] text_end
